                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13970: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-28T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 28, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 28—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>245. I am reliably informed that in a secret meeting of the Council this morning
                    a resolution along the lines reported in my telegram 242, September 27, 5 p.m.,
                    was opposed by Belgium and Sweden on the ground that it was inconsistent with
                    their declared policies respecting article 16. The resolution has again been
                    referred to a <pb facs="0519" n="515" xml:id="pg_515"/> drafting committee which
                    will endeavor to meet this objection. The Chinese delegate informs me that the
                    question is one of wording but not of substance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucknell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
